        the first nation to hold two World Cups by hosting the<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1986_FIFA_World_Cup" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" title="1986 FIFA World Cup">1986 World Cup</a><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;">. 
        The format changed again, with the second round being replaced by a pre-quarterfinal, knockout competition, for which 16 teams would qualify. It was also decided that the final two matches in all groups would kick off simultaneously, to ensure complete fairness.<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canada_men's_national_soccer_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" title="Canada men's national soccer team">Canada</a><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;">,<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Denmark_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" title="Denmark national football team">Denmark</a><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;"><span>&nbsp;</span>and<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" title="Iraq national football team">Iraq</a><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;"><span>&nbsp;</span>made 
        their first finals.<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/José_Batista" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" title="José Batista">José Batista</a><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;"><span>&nbsp;</span>of 
        Uruguay set a World Cup record being sent off after a mere 56 seconds into the game against Scotland. The quarterfinal match between England and Argentina is remembered for two remarkable<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diego_Maradona" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" title="Diego Maradona">Diego Maradona</a><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;"><span>&nbsp;</span>goals, 
        later regarded as player of the tournament, the first, the controversial<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a class="mw-redirect" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hand_of_God_goal" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" title="Hand of God goal">handball goal</a><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;">, 
        and the second, considered to be the<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a class="mw-redirect" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goal_of_the_Century" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" title="Goal of the Century">Goal of the Century</a><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;">, 
        in which he dribbled half the length of the field past five English players before scoring. In the final, Argentina beat West Germany 3–2, inspired by Diego Maradona, who set up<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jorge_Burruchaga" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" title="Jorge Burruchaga">Jorge Burruchaga</a><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;"><span>&nbsp;</span>for 
        the winner.</span></p>
    <h3 style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><span id="The_1990s" class="mw-headline">The 1990s</span></h3>
    <p style="margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
        The<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1990_FIFA_World_Cup" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="1990 FIFA World Cup">1990 World Cup</a><span>&nbsp;</span>was held in Italy. Cameroon, participating in their second World Cup, made it to the quarter-finals after beating Argentina in the opening game. No African country had ever reached the quarter-finals before. Mexico was unable to compete in the<span>&nbsp;</span><a class="mw-redirect" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1990_FIFA_World_Cup_(qualification)" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="1990 FIFA World Cup (qualification)">1990 World Cup preliminary</a><span>&nbsp;</span>competition as a result of a two-year ban for age fraud at a youth championship, an incident known as<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cachirules" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Cachirules">Los 
        Cachirules</a>. the United States qualified for the first time since 1950. An unpleasant episode marred the<span>&nbsp;</span><a class="mw-redirect" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1990_FIFA_World_Cup_(qualification_CONMEBOL)" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="1990 FIFA World Cup (qualification CONMEBOL)">South American qualifiers</a>: during the match between Brazil and<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chile_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Chile national football team">Chile</a>, a firework landed close to the Chilean goalkeeper<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roberto_Rojas_(Chilean_footballer)" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Roberto Rojas (Chilean footballer)">Roberto Rojas</a>, who then feigned injury by cutting his own face with a razor blade he had hidden in his glove. His 
        team refused to continue the match (as they were down a goal at the time).<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/El_Maracanazo" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="El Maracanazo">The plot was discovered</a><span>&nbsp;</span>and resulted in a 12-year suspension for Rojas and to Chile being banned from the 1994 World Cup.<sup id="cite_ref-26" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_the_FIFA_World_Cup#cite_note-26" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;">[26]</a></sup><span>&nbsp;</span>The final featured the same teams as in 1986. After finishing runners-up in the two previous tournaments, West Germany beat Argentina 1–0 in the final to record their third title. The<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republic_of_Ireland_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Republic of Ireland national football team">Republic 
        of Ireland</a><span>&nbsp;</span>also made their first appearance in the tournament, reaching the quarter-finals without winning a single game (four draws, with a penalty shoot-out win over Romania in the second round). This is the furthest a team has ever advanced in the World Cup without winning a game.</p>
    <p style="margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
        The<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1994_FIFA_World_Cup" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="1994 FIFA World Cup">1994 World Cup</a>, held in the United States, saw the first World Cup final to be decided on penalties, with Brazil edging out Italy.<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serbia_and_Montenegro_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Serbia and Montenegro national football team">FR Yugoslavia</a><span>&nbsp;</span>was excluded due to<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Nations_Security_Council_Resolution_757" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="United Nations Security Council Resolution 757">UN sanctions</a><span>&nbsp;</span>in connection with the<span>&nbsp;</span><a class="mw-redirect" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bosnian_war" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Bosnian war">war 
        in Bosnia-Herzegovina</a>. Colombia qualified<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Argentina_v_Colombia_(1994_FIFA_World_Cup_qualification)" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Argentina v Colombia (1994 FIFA World Cup qualification)">unexpectedly defeating Argentina 5-0</a>.<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Japan national football team">Japan</a><span>&nbsp;</span>narrowly missed a ticket to the World Cup after drawing with<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Iraq national football team">Iraq</a><span>&nbsp;</span>in the final match of the qualification round, remembered by fans as the &quot;<a class="mw-redirect" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1993_Japan_v_Iraq_football_match" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="1993 Japan v Iraq football match">Agony 
        of Doha</a>&quot;. As a result,<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Korea_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="South Korea national football team">South Korea</a><span>&nbsp;</span>qualified to the tournament.<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russia_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Russia national football team">Russia</a><span>&nbsp;</span>(taking the place of the Soviet Union which had disintegrated over 1990 and 1991) played their first World Cup competition as a new country, with<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greece_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Greece national football team">Greece</a>,<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nigeria_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Nigeria national football team">Nigeria</a><span>&nbsp;</span>and<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabia_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Saudi Arabia national football team">Saudi 
        Arabia</a><span>&nbsp;</span>as the other first-timers. Diego Maradona was banned mid-tournament after testing positive for<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cocaine" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Cocaine">cocaine</a>: without him, Argentina were eliminated in the last 16 by<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Romania_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Romania national football team">Romania</a>. Despite soccer&#39;s relative lack of popularity in the host nation, the tournament was the most financially successful<sup id="cite_ref-27" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_the_FIFA_World_Cup#cite_note-27" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;">[27]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-28" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_the_FIFA_World_Cup#cite_note-28" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;">[28]</a></sup><span>&nbsp;</span>in 
        World Cup history; it broke tournament records with overall attendance of 3,587,538 and an average of 68,991 per match,<sup id="cite_ref-29" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_the_FIFA_World_Cup#cite_note-29" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;">[29]</a></sup><span>&nbsp;</span>marks that stood unbroken as of 2018<sup id="cite_ref-FIFA_Records_30-0" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_the_FIFA_World_Cup#cite_note-FIFA_Records-30" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;">[30]</a></sup><span>&nbsp;</span>despite the expansion of the competition from 24 to 32 teams starting with the<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1998_FIFA_World_Cup" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="1998 FIFA World Cup">1998 
        World Cup</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-31" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_the_FIFA_World_Cup#cite_note-31" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;">[31]</a></sup></p>
    <p style="margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
        The total attendance for the tournament of nearly 3.6 million remains the biggest in World Cup history.<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oleg_Salenko" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Oleg Salenko">Oleg Salenko</a><span>&nbsp;</span>of Russia became the first player to score five goals in a single World Cup finals game in his country&#39;s 6–1 group stage win over Cameroon. In the same match, 42-year-old<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roger_Milla" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Roger Milla">Roger Milla</a><span>&nbsp;</span>scored the only goal for Cameroon, becoming the oldest player ever to score in a World Cup match.<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hristo_Stoichkov" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Hristo Stoichkov">Hristo Stoichkov</a><span>&nbsp;</span>shared the Golden Boot as the joint top 
        goal scorer in the tournament with Oleg Salenko (six goals), as well as earning the Bronze Ball award. He led Bulgaria to a shock 2–1 win over defending champions Germany in the quarter-finals, before losing 2–1 to Italy and losing the third place play-off to Sweden, 4–0.</p>
    <p style="margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
        The<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1998_FIFA_World_Cup" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="1998 FIFA World Cup">1998 World Cup</a><span>&nbsp;</span>was held in France, and had an expanded format featuring 32 teams. Iran beat the<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maldives_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Maldives national football team">Maldives</a><span>&nbsp;</span>in<span>&nbsp;</span><a class="mw-redirect" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1998_FIFA_World_Cup_(qualification_AFC)" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="1998 FIFA World Cup (qualification AFC)">qualification</a><span>&nbsp;</span>by the widest margin in World Cup history – 17–0. In the finals, the second round match between France and Paraguay witnessed the first<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_goal" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Golden goal">golden 
        goal</a><span>&nbsp;</span>in World Cup history, as<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laurent_Blanc" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Laurent Blanc">Laurent Blanc</a><span>&nbsp;</span>scored to give the hosts a 1–0 victory. Hosts France won the tournament by beating Brazil 3–0 in the final, with Brazilian star player<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ronaldo_(Brazilian_footballer)" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)">Ronaldo</a><span>&nbsp;</span>being controversially capped for the match after having had a seizure hours before kickoff. Debutants<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Croatia_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Croatia national football team">Croatia</a><span>&nbsp;</span>finished a commendable third.</p>
    <h3 style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><span id="The_2000s" class="mw-headline">The 2000s</span></h3>
    <p style="margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
        The<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2002_FIFA_World_Cup" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="2002 FIFA World Cup">2002 World Cup</a><span>&nbsp;</span>was the first to be held in Asia, and was hosted jointly by South Korea and Japan. Togolese<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Souleymane_Mamam" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Souleymane Mamam">Souleymane Mamam</a><span>&nbsp;</span>became the youngest player ever to take to a World Cup preliminary game field at 13 years, 310 days in Lomé in May 2001. Australia defeated<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_Samoa_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="American Samoa national football team">American Samoa</a><span>&nbsp;</span>31–0 in a preliminary match – a new record for the margin of victory, and the highest-scoring match ever. 
        The tournament was a successful one for teams traditionally regarded as minnows, with<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Korea_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="South Korea national football team">South Korea</a>,<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Senegal_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Senegal national football team">Senegal</a><span>&nbsp;</span>and the United States all reaching the last eight. Brazil beat Germany 2–0 in the final for their fifth title. The<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkey_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Turkey national football team">Turkish</a><span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hakan_Şükür" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Hakan Şükür">Hakan 
        Sukur</a><span>&nbsp;</span>made history by scoring the earliest World Cup goal of all time against South Korea at only 11 seconds.</p>
    <p style="margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
        The<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2006_FIFA_World_Cup" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="2006 FIFA World Cup">2006 World Cup</a><span>&nbsp;</span>was held in Germany. It was the first World Cup for which the previous winner had to qualify; the host nation(s) continue to receive an automatic berth. Four African teams also made their debut in the world cup finals:<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Togo_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Togo national football team">Togo</a>,<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ivory_Coast_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Ivory Coast national football team">Ivory Coast</a>,<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angola_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Angola national football team">Angola</a><span>&nbsp;</span>and<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ghana_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Ghana national football team">Ghana</a><span>&nbsp;</span>who 
        impressively made it to last 16 by beating the<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Czech_Republic_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Czech Republic national football team">Czech Republic</a>, third ranked in the world, 2–1, along with the United States 2–0, before losing to the defending champions Brazil 0–3.</p>
    <p style="margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
        First seed and holders Brazil and second seeded England were initially English bookmakers&#39; favourites. A strong performance by Germany brought them as far as the semi-finals. However, the final match-up was between Italy and France, in which French captain<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zinedine_Zidane" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Zinedine Zidane">Zinedine Zidane</a><span>&nbsp;</span>was sent off in the last ten minutes of extra time for a<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Headbutt" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Headbutt">headbutt</a><span>&nbsp;</span>to the chest of Italian central defender<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marco_Materazzi" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none;" title="Marco Materazzi">Marco Materazzi</a>. Italy went on to win 5–3 in a penalty shootout, the score having been 1–1 
        after 90 minutes and extra time.</p>
    <h3 style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><span id="The_2010s" class="mw-headline">The 2010s</span></h3>
    <p style="margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
        <span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;">The<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2010_FIFA_World_Cup" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" title="2010 FIFA World Cup">2010 
        World Cup</a><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;"><span>&nbsp;</span>was held in South Africa. It was the first cup hosted on African soil, and the cup was won by<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spain_national_football_team" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" title="Spain national football team">Spain</a><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;">. 
        The tournament was noted for its highly defensive opening matches, controversies surrounding goal-line technology, and the introduction of<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vuvuzela" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" title="Vuvuzela">vuvuzelas</a><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;">. 
        Though considered as one of the tournament favorites, the Spaniards won the cup despite scoring only eight goals in seven games and losing their opening match to Switzerland.<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Villa" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" title="David Villa">David Villa</a><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;"><span>&nbsp;</span>led 
